Package: clinriskr
Title: Reproducible Binary Outcome Analysis for Small Clinical Cohorts
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("ClinRiskR", "Contributors",
           email = "303987942+baidu1giao-dot@users.noreply.github.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a privacy-conscious, reproducible workflow for binary
    outcome analyses in small clinical cohorts. It validates tabular inputs,
    creates descriptive summaries, fits conventional and Firth logistic
    regression models, evaluates apparent discrimination and calibration, and
    writes an auditable set of tables, figures, and session metadata. A fully
    synthetic hypertensive-disorders-of-pregnancy example is included.
